# TDD Workflow

## When to Activate
- Writing test cases before implementation (test-writer)
- Sanity checking test coverage against acceptance criteria (PO/PM)
- Implementing code to pass failing tests (frontend-dev, backend-dev)
- Verifying test results post-implementation (qa-reviewer)

## Core Concepts

TDD in this system follows a 4-phase flow with a quality gate between test writing and implementation.

## Phase Flow

### Red Phase (test-writer)
1. Convert ticket acceptance criteria into test cases
2. Cover happy path + error path + edge cases
3. Run tests — all tests must FAIL
4. Save files: `__tests__/{feature}/{ticket-id}.test.ts`
5. Name test cases to clearly map to acceptance criteria

### Gate Phase (po-pm)
1. Verify test cases map 1:1 to acceptance criteria
2. Check for missing acceptance criteria coverage
3. Check for tests not in the spec
4. PASS/FAIL decision (FAIL allows 1 revision, re-failure escalates to Human)

### Green Phase (frontend-dev / backend-dev)
1. Review test files
2. Implement minimal code to pass tests
3. Run tests — all tests must PASS
4. Remove unnecessary code (YAGNI)

### Verify Phase (qa-reviewer)
- **Standard QA (Medium/Large)**: E2E tests + integration tests + Visual QA + code review + scoring
- **Lite QA (Small)**: Unit test pass check + code review + Visual QA Level 1 (no scoring)

## Guidelines
1. Tests must be committed in failing state — implementation agents turn them green
2. Each test case name must clearly reference its acceptance criterion
3. Do not test behavior not described in the spec
4. Target unit test coverage: 80%+

## Integration
- test-writer: Primary user (Red phase)
- po-pm: Gate phase (Sanity Check)
- frontend-dev, backend-dev: Green phase
- qa-reviewer: Verify phase
